transcript.text: Welcome to on Print Shop.
In this video, we'll explore the latest enhancements to the quote feature, covering updates on both the front end and the admin panel.
These new capabilities are designed to simplify the quoting process, improve accuracy, and enhance the overall user experience for both admins and customers.
Let's begin with one of the most powerful updates, the introduction of smart quotes for admins through a new quote type called Configurable Product.
In the past, admins needed to manually create custom fields and calculate prices for each quote, which was time consuming and error prone.
With this new feature, admins can now select a product, define dimensions and quantity, and choose from preconfigured options that already include pricing formulas.
The system calculates the price automatically and displays a real time price summary, making the process faster and far more accurate.
To make option selection even more efficient, we've introduced option tags.
These allow admins to group commonly used product options and a reusable labels such as business card or package options.
Once A tag is selected, all associated options are applied instantly and the pricing summary updates automatically.
This feature helps reduce repetitive selections and ensures consistency across quotes.
We've also made usability improvements to the quote form page.
Previously, all fields were displayed in a single column, making the form appear long and cluttered.
The new design supports A2 column layout, offering a more organized and user friendly interface.
Admins can configure the layout from the settings to display one or two fields per row, and this layout applies to both the front store quote form and the offline quote form.
To enhance form structure, we've introduced the ability to group fields within the quote form.
Related fields can now be grouped under specific headers, making it easier for users to understand and fill out the form.
This grouping functionality is supported on both the customer facing and admin interfaces.
If a product already has groups configured at the product level, they will now automatically appear in the quote form.
Next, let's look at the enhancements made to the Quote detail page.
Previously, customer and product information were displayed in separate sections, making it harder to navigate.
The new layout improves the flow by aligning product details and pricing inputs more logically, making it easier to manage and update quotes.
We've also added a second tab titled Quote Updates, which automates status changes throughout the quote life cycle.
For example, updating the pricing and sending a message to the customer will update the status to quotation.
To improve visibility into quote activity, we've introduced a Quote History section.
This log captures all changes, updates, and interactions related to a quote in one centralized place, allowing admins to track the quote's progress and history more effectively.
Another time saving feature is the duplicate quote function.
Admins can now quickly replicate an existing quote and assign it to another customer within the same store.
This is especially useful for handling similar or recurring requests without having to recreate everything from scratch.
These enhancements are aimed at simplifying the quote creation process, saving time, and ensuring consistency across the board.
We hope you find these updates helpful in managing your quotes more efficiently.
We hope these updates bring greater flexibility and efficiency to your quoting process.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through livechatononprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
